<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>INTER.act - Combined Presentation</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@300;400;500;700;800&family=Space+Grotesk:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" />
    <style>
      /* Combined-only: scroll-snap + progress bar + nav dots */
      html {
        scroll-snap-type: y mandatory;
        scroll-behavior: smooth;
      }
      body {
        overflow-y: auto;
      }
      .slide {
        scroll-snap-align: start;
      }
      .reveal {
        animation: none;
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateY(20px);
        transition:
          opacity 0.7s var(--ease),
          transform 0.7s var(--ease);
      }
      .slide.visible .reveal {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateY(0);
      }
      .slide.visible .reveal:nth-child(1) {
        transition-delay: 0.05s;
      }
      .slide.visible .reveal:nth-child(2) {
        transition-delay: 0.15s;
      }
      .slide.visible .reveal:nth-child(3) {
        transition-delay: 0.25s;
      }
      .slide.visible .reveal:nth-child(4) {
        transition-delay: 0.35s;
      }
      .slide.visible .reveal:nth-child(5) {
        transition-delay: 0.45s;
      }
      .slide.visible .reveal:nth-child(6) {
        transition-delay: 0.55s;
      }
      .slide.visible .reveal:nth-child(7) {
        transition-delay: 0.65s;
      }

      .progress-bar {
        position: fixed;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        height: 2px;
        background: var(--green);
        z-index: 1000;
        transition: width 0.2s linear;
        box-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--green-glow);
      }
      .nav-dots {
        position: fixed;
        right: clamp(0.6rem, 1.5vw, 1.5rem);
        top: 50%;
        transform: translateY(-50%);
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.6rem;
        z-index: 100;
      }
      .nav-dots button {
        width: 8px;
        height: 8px;
        border-radius: 50%;
        background: var(--border-bright);
        border: none;
        cursor: pointer;
        padding: 0;
        transition: all 0.3s var(--ease);
      }
      .nav-dots button.active {
        background: var(--green);
        box-shadow: 0 0 12px var(--green-glow);
        transform: scale(1.3);
      }
      /* Hide chrome navigation links inside combined view */
      .slide .chrome .branch a {
        display: none;
      }

      /* Architecture slide fit */
      #arch-slide-fix .slide-content {
        justify-content: flex-start;
        gap: clamp(0.6rem, 1.5vh, 1.2rem);
        padding-top: clamp(1.5rem, 4.5vh, 3rem) !important;
      }
      #arch-slide-fix .section-title {
        margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
      }
      #arch-slide-fix .arch {
        padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
      }
      #arch-slide-fix .arch-svg {
        max-height: clamp(180px, 34vh, 340px);
      }
      #arch-slide-fix .arch.diagram-frame {
        cursor: pointer;
        position: relative;
      }
      #arch-slide-fix .arch-callout {
        margin-top: 0;
        padding: 0.8rem 1.2rem !important;
        font-size: clamp(0.75rem, 1.1vw, 0.9rem) !important;
        line-height: 1.4 !important;
      }

      /* Goal slide fit */
      #goal-slide-fix .slide-content {
        margin-top: clamp(1.5rem, 4vh, 2.5rem);
        justify-content: flex-start;
        gap: clamp(0.4rem, 1vw, 0.8rem);
      }
      #goal-slide-fix .section-title {
        margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
      }
      #goal-slide-fix p.muted {
        font-size: clamp(0.75rem, 1.1vw, 0.95rem);
        line-height: 1.5;
        max-width: 72ch !important;
      }
      #goal-slide-fix .diagram-frame {
        margin-top: 0.5rem;
        max-height: clamp(300px, 55vh, 520px);
      }
      #goal-slide-fix .diagram-frame object,
      #goal-slide-fix .diagram-frame img {
        max-height: clamp(280px, 52vh, 480px);
      }
      #goal-slide-fix .arch-callout {
        margin-top: 0.3rem;
        padding: 0.6rem 1rem !important;
        font-size: clamp(0.72rem, 1vw, 0.88rem) !important;
        line-height: 1.45 !important;
      }

      /* Built slide fit */
      #built-slide-fix .slide-content {
        justify-content: flex-start;
        gap: clamp(0.4rem, 1vh, 0.8rem);
        padding-top: clamp(1.5rem, 4vh, 2.5rem);
      }
      #built-slide-fix .section-title {
        margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
      }
      #built-slide-fix .arch-callout {
        margin-top: 0.2rem !important;
        padding: 0.6rem 1rem !important;
        font-size: clamp(0.7rem, 0.9vw, 0.85rem) !important;
      }

      /* Fix legend wrapping */
      .arch-legend-item {
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      /* Lightbox refinement */
      .lightbox {
        align-items: center !important;
        justify-content: center !important;
        padding: 2rem !important;
        overflow-y: auto !important;
      }
      .lightbox object,
      .lightbox img {
        width: 98vw !important;
        max-width: none !important;
        height: auto !important;
        max-height: 94vh !important;
        object-fit: contain !important;
        transform: none !important;
        margin: 0 auto !important;
        background: white;
        border-radius: 4px;
      }
      .lightbox .close-hint {
        z-index: 10001 !important;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2) !important;
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5) !important;
        color: #ffffff !important;
        padding: 0.5rem 1rem !important;
        border-radius: 6px !important;
        opacity: 1 !important;
        display: block !important;
        pointer-events: auto !important;
      }
      .arch-lightbox-inner {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
      }
      .arch-lightbox-inner svg {
        background: white;
        border-radius: 4px;
      }

      /* ===========================================
         INTRODUCTION SLIDE (Imagine - warehouse base)
         =========================================== */
      .intro-slide .slide-content {
        justify-content: flex-start;
        gap: clamp(0.5rem, 1.2vw, 1rem);
        overflow: visible;
      }

      .intro-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr;
        gap: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 5rem);
        align-items: center;
        flex: 1;
        min-height: 0;
        overflow: visible;
      }
      @media (max-width: 720px) {
        .intro-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
        .intro-warehouse {
          order: -1;
          justify-content: center;
        }
        .intro-warehouse-frame {
          margin-left: auto;
          margin-right: auto;
        }
      }

      .intro-story {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: clamp(0.5rem, 1.1vw, 0.9rem);
      }
      .intro-story p {
        font-size: clamp(0.8rem, 1.25vw, 1.05rem);
        line-height: 1.55;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        max-width: 65ch;
      }
      .intro-story p strong {
        color: var(--text-primary);
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      .intro-story p .green-accent {
        color: var(--green);
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      .intro-traits {
        list-style: none;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: clamp(0.3rem, 0.8vw, 0.6rem);
        margin-top: calc(0.5 * var(--element-gap));
      }
      .intro-traits li {
        font-family: var(--font-mono);
        font-size: var(--small-size);
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        padding: 0.5em 0.7em;
        background: var(--bg-panel);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-left: 2px solid var(--green);
        border-radius: 4px;
        line-height: 1.4;
      }

      .intro-pivot {
        font-family: var(--font-display);
        font-size: clamp(0.9rem, 1.4vw, 1.15rem);
        line-height: 1.45;
        color: var(--text-primary);
        margin-top: calc(0.5 * var(--element-gap));
        padding-left: clamp(0.6rem, 1.2vw, 1rem);
        border-left: 3px solid var(--green);
      }

      /* ----- Porthole-framed warehouse image ----- */
      .intro-warehouse {
        position: relative;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        margin-top: -1rem;
        justify-self: center;
        padding: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem);
        aspect-ratio: 1;
        max-height: 100%;
        min-height: 0;
        overflow: visible;
      }

      .intro-warehouse-frame {
        position: relative;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        max-width: clamp(240px, 32vw, 420px);
        max-height: clamp(240px, 32vw, 420px);
        aspect-ratio: 1;
        margin-left: auto;
        margin-right: auto;
        border-radius: 50%;
        box-shadow:
          inset 0 0 0 5px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55),
          inset 0 0 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.28),
          0 0 0 1.5px rgba(45, 164, 78, 0.55),
          0 0 60px rgba(45, 164, 78, 0.22),
          0 18px 36px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18);
        z-index: 2;
      }
      .intro-warehouse-frame img {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        object-fit: cover;
        display: block;
        border-radius: 50%;
        filter: contrast(1.04) saturate(0.95);
      }
      .intro-warehouse-glass {
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        border-radius: 50%;
        background: radial-gradient(
          circle at 30% 25%,
          rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.32) 0%,
          rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08) 22%,
          transparent 38%
        );
        pointer-events: none;
        z-index: 3;
      }

      /* Peer-mesh decoration: 8 actor nodes around the warehouse,
         connected by faint chord lines. Reinforces the INTER.act
         coordination metaphor instead of planet-orbit imagery. */
      .intro-warehouse-mesh {
        position: absolute;
        inset: -34px;
        pointer-events: none;
        z-index: 1;
        overflow: visible;
      }
      .intro-warehouse-mesh circle.node {
        fill: var(--green);
        filter: drop-shadow(0 0 4px rgba(45, 164, 78, 0.7));
      }
      .intro-warehouse-mesh circle.node.pulse {
        animation: mesh-pulse 2.4s var(--ease) infinite;
        transform-box: fill-box;
        transform-origin: center;
      }
      .intro-warehouse-mesh circle.node.pulse-2 {
        animation-delay: 0.8s;
      }
      .intro-warehouse-mesh circle.node.pulse-3 {
        animation-delay: 1.6s;
      }
      .intro-warehouse-mesh line.chord {
        stroke: rgba(45, 164, 78, 0.28);
        stroke-width: 0.5;
        stroke-dasharray: 2 2;
      }
      .intro-warehouse-mesh circle.ring {
        fill: none;
        stroke: rgba(45, 164, 78, 0.22);
        stroke-width: 0.4;
        stroke-dasharray: 1 3;
      }
      @keyframes mesh-pulse {
        0%,
        100% {
          transform: scale(1);
          opacity: 0.85;
        }
        50% {
          transform: scale(1.6);
          opacity: 1;
        }
      }
      @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
        .intro-warehouse-mesh circle.node.pulse {
          animation: none;
        }
      }

      /* Demo-slide factory row */
      .demo-factory .node .label,
      .demo-factory .node .role {
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      /* ==========================================================
         SLIDE 2 - INTRODUCTION
         ========================================================== */
      .intro-page .slide-content {
        justify-content: center;
        gap: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.5rem);
      }
      .intro-page .lede {
        font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.55vw, 1.25rem);
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: var(--text-primary);
        max-width: 88ch;
        font-weight: 400;
      }
      .intro-page .lede strong {
        color: var(--green);
        font-weight: 700;
      }
      .intro-cards {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: clamp(0.7rem, 1.6vw, 1.2rem);
        margin-top: var(--element-gap);
      }
      @media (max-width: 800px) {
        .intro-cards {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
      }
      .intro-card {
        padding: 0.85em 1.05em;
        background: var(--bg-panel);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 6px;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.4em;
      }
      .intro-card.problem {
        border-left: 3px solid var(--magenta);
      }
      .intro-card.walk {
        border-left: 3px solid var(--green);
      }
      .intro-card .label {
        font-family: var(--font-mono);
        font-size: 0.72rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        color: var(--text-dim);
      }
      .intro-card.problem .label {
        color: var(--magenta);
      }
      .intro-card.walk .label {
        color: var(--green);
      }
      .intro-card p {
        font-size: clamp(0.88rem, 1.25vw, 1rem);
        line-height: 1.55;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        margin: 0;
      }
      .intro-card p strong {
        color: var(--text-primary);
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      .intro-card ul {
        list-style: none;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 0.35em 1em;
      }
      .intro-card ul li {
        font-family: var(--font-mono);
        font-size: 0.82rem;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        position: relative;
        padding-left: 1em;
        line-height: 1.45;
      }
      .intro-card ul li::before {
        content: "▸";
        position: absolute;
        left: 0;
        color: var(--green);
      }
      .intro-card ul li em {
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--text-dim);
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="progress-bar" id="progress"></div>
    <nav class="nav-dots" id="navDots" aria-label="Slide navigation"></nav>

    <!-- =============================================
     SLIDE 1 - TITLE COVER
     ============================================= -->
    <section class="slide title-cover">
      <header class="chrome">
        <span class="dot r"></span><span class="dot y"></span
        ><span class="dot g"></span>
        <span class="path">~/Inter-Act/01-title</span>
        <span class="branch"></span>
      </header>

      <div class="slide-content">
        <div class="hero-banner">
          <img
            src="assets/Main DIgitech Banner.png"
            alt="Digital Technologies - Zukunft. Digital. Nachhaltig."
          />
        </div>

        <div class="cover-body">
          <div class="cover-main">
            <div class="cover-left">
              <div class="term">SoSe 2026</div>
              <div class="product">Inter.act</div>
            </div>
            <div class="brand-row">
              <img
                src="assets/IN3 logo.png"
                alt="IN³ - Intelligent Innovation &amp; Integration"
              />
              <span class="x">x</span>
              <img src="assets/Aisune logo.png" alt="AiSuNe Foundation" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="partners-strip">
            <div class="partners-left">
              <img
                src="assets/Ostfalia & clausthal logo.png"
                alt="Ein gemeinsames Studienprogramm der · Ostfalia · TU Clausthal"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="partners-right">
              <svg
                class="ig-icon"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                aria-hidden="true"
              >
                <rect
                  x="2.5"
                  y="2.5"
                  width="19"
                  height="19"
                  rx="5"
                  stroke="#bf3989"
                  stroke-width="2"
                />
                <circle
                  cx="12"
                  cy="12"
                  r="4"
                  stroke="#bf3989"
                  stroke-width="2"
                />
                <circle cx="17.5" cy="6.5" r="1.2" fill="#bf3989" />
              </svg>
              <span>digitecstudieren.de</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="slide-number" style="color: #888">
        01<span class="of"> / 10</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- =============================================
     SLIDE 2 - INTRODUCTION
     Rephrased per Alex: digital twin, not factory simulator.
     Problem reframed: real driver is COMPLEXITY → DEADLOCK, not latency/links/compute.
     Goal: non-deterministic, self-developing solutions.
     ============================================= -->
    <section class="slide intro-page">
      <header class="chrome">
        <span class="dot r"></span><span class="dot y"></span
        ><span class="dot g"></span>
        <span class="path">~/Inter-Act/02-introduction</span>
        <span class="branch"></span>
      </header>

      <div class="slide-content">
        <p class="eyebrow reveal">Introduction</p>
        <h2 class="section-title reveal">
          What is INTER<span style="color: var(--green)">.</span>act?
        </h2>

        <p class="reveal lede">
          Inter.act is the <strong>digital twin</strong> of an autonomous robot
          warehouse where every actor -
          <strong>arm, vehicle, conveyor</strong> - carries its own small AI
          brain and self-organizes with its neighbours to complete tasks that no
          single actor could do alone, instead of waiting for a central
          controller to tell it what to do.
        </p>

        <div class="intro-cards reveal">
          <div class="intro-card problem">
            <span class="label">The problem we're working on</span>
            <p>
              A single central controller cannot keep up with
              <strong>growing system complexity</strong>. With many actors and
              unpredictable combinations of states, you cannot pre-define every
              outcome - and the system <strong>deadlocks</strong> on situations
              the controller was never programmed for.
            </p>
            <p>
              Our goal is a system that finds
              <span class="green-accent"
                >non-deterministic solutions on its own</span
              >
              - one that self-develops a way forward, without every path being
              hard-coded ahead of time.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="intro-card walk">
            <span class="label">We'll walk you through</span>
            <ul>
              <li>Why we picked this problem</li>
              <li>Where we want to land</li>
              <li>What we've built <em>(live demo)</em></li>
              <li>What comes next</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="slide-number">02<span class="of"> / 10</span></div>
    </section>

    <!-- =============================================
     SLIDE 3 - IMAGINE (warehouse base opener)
     Per Alex: removed "These actors are autonomous" sentence -
     it contradicts the flow (next sentence says current approach
     is central). That sentence moves to slide 4 as conclusion.
     ============================================= -->
    <section class="slide intro-slide">
      <header class="chrome">
        <span class="dot r"></span><span class="dot y"></span
        ><span class="dot g"></span>
        <span class="path">~/Inter-Act/03-imagine</span>
        <span class="branch"></span>
      </header>

      <div class="slide-content">
        <p class="eyebrow reveal">Imagine</p>
        <h2 class="section-title reveal">
          Inside the <span style="color: var(--green)">warehouse</span>
        </h2>

        <div class="intro-grid">
          <div class="intro-story reveal">
            <p>
              The actors on the floor are
              <strong>robotic arms, shuttle vehicles, and conveyor belts</strong
              >. Each one does its own job: arms pick and place, shuttles move
              parts between zones, belts carry parts across longer distances.
              <strong
                >Different jobs, different expertise, all working in the same
                place at the same time.</strong
              >
            </p>

            <p>
              With the current approach, you need
              <strong>one central controller</strong> coordinating every actor
              at once. That works fine on a small or mid-size setup.
              <span class="green-accent"
                >A single controller stops scaling</span
              >
              once you add a large amount of actors - because of latency,
              unreliable links, and the computational power demanded from a
              single system.
            </p>

            <ul class="intro-traits">
              <li>Different actors,<br />different tasks</li>
              <li>Demanding environment,<br />outside influences</li>
              <li>Latency &amp; unreliable<br />links</li>
              <li>Computation scales<br />exponentially</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="intro-pivot reveal">
              So what if it's not one central unit at all?
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="intro-warehouse reveal" aria-hidden="true">
            <div class="intro-warehouse-frame">
              <img
                src="assets/warehouse.png"
                alt="A base in warehouse - multiple actors with their own jobs"
              />
              <span class="intro-warehouse-glass"></span>
              <svg
                class="intro-warehouse-mesh"
                viewBox="0 0 200 200"
                aria-hidden="true"
              >
                <circle class="ring" cx="100" cy="100" r="98" />
                <line class="chord" x1="100" y1="2" x2="195.7" y2="138.6" />
                <line class="chord" x1="195.7" y1="61.4" x2="4.3" y2="138.6" />
                <line class="chord" x1="198" y1="100" x2="30.7" y2="30.7" />
                <line
                  class="chord"
                  x1="169.3"
                  y1="169.3"
                  x2="30.7"
                  y2="169.3"
                />
                <line class="chord" x1="100" y1="198" x2="4.3" y2="61.4" />
                <circle class="node pulse" cx="100" cy="2" r="3" />
                <circle class="node" cx="169.3" cy="30.7" r="2.4" />
                <circle class="node pulse-2" cx="198" cy="100" r="3" />
                <circle class="node" cx="169.3" cy="169.3" r="2.4" />
                <circle class="node pulse-3" cx="100" cy="198" r="3" />
                <circle class="node" cx="30.7" cy="169.3" r="2.4" />
                <circle class="node pulse" cx="2" cy="100" r="3" />
                <circle class="node" cx="30.7" cy="30.7" r="2.4" />
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="slide-number">03<span class="of"> / 10</span></div>
    </section>

    <!-- =============================================
     SLIDE 4 - ULTIMATE GOAL
     Per Alex: conclusion sentence added below diagram.
     Observer description refined. All "asset" → "actor".
     ============================================= -->
    <section class="slide" id="goal-slide-fix">
      <header class="chrome">
        <span class="dot r"></span><span class="dot y"></span
        ><span class="dot g"></span>
        <span class="path">~/Inter-Act/04-goal</span>
        <span class="branch"></span>
      </header>

      <div class="slide-content">
        <p class="eyebrow reveal">Ultimate goal</p>
        <h2 class="section-title reveal">
          One central controller <span style="color: var(--text-dim)">→</span>
          <span style="color: var(--green)">brains that negotiate</span>
        </h2>

        <p class="reveal muted" style="max-width: 80ch">
          Today every decision flows through one deterministic central
          controller - no intelligence, no autonomy.
          <br /><br /><strong>BUT</strong> in INTER.act, every actor reasons on
          its own and works out handovers with its neighbours directly.
        </p>

        <!-- Today vs INTER.act diagram - click to enlarge -->
        <div
          class="diagram-frame reveal"
          id="diagramFrame"
          role="button"
          tabindex="0"
          aria-label="Click to enlarge diagram"
        >
          <span class="zoom-hint">click to zoom ⤢</span>
          <object
            type="image/svg+xml"
            data="assets/today-vs-interact.svg"
            aria-label="Today versus INTER.act architecture diagram"
          >
            <img
              src="assets/today-vs-interact.svg"
              alt="Today versus INTER.act architecture diagram"
            />
          </object>
        </div>

        <div class="arch-callout reveal">
          <strong>Conclusion:</strong> these actors are autonomous - no human
          issues commands, each one decides for itself what to do next.
          Peer-to-peer messaging between brains swaps information directly on
          a shared message bus. Actors negotiate handovers; the observer
          <strong>sets the goal</strong>, watches state, and stays out of the
          way. This setup is a <strong>foundation</strong> - while shown here
          in a warehouse, the same coordination model extends naturally to
          other multi-agent environments such as autonomous drones or even
          space-based systems.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="slide-number">04<span class="of"> / 10</span></div>
    </section>

    <!-- =============================================
     SLIDE 5 - PROJECT PHASES
     Per Alex: "asset communication" → "actor coordination".
     "per station" → "per actor". "every arm" → "every actor".
     ============================================= -->
    <section class="slide">
      <header class="chrome">
        <span class="dot r"></span><span class="dot y"></span
        ><span class="dot g"></span>
        <span class="path">~/Inter-Act/05-phases</span>
        <span class="branch"></span>
      </header>

      <div class="slide-content">
        <p class="eyebrow reveal">Project phases</p>
        <h2 class="section-title reveal">
          Three epics <span style="color: var(--text-dim)">·</span>
          <span style="color: var(--amber)">we are here</span>
        </h2>
        <p
          class="reveal dim"
          style="
            font-family: var(--font-mono);
            font-size: var(--small-size);
            margin-top: calc(-1 * var(--element-gap));
          "
        >
          Sprint 1-2 · foundation laid &nbsp;·&nbsp; Sprint 3 · AI integration
          &nbsp;·&nbsp; Sprint 4+ · actor coordination
        </p>

        <div class="phases reveal">
          <div class="phase done">
            <div class="phase-head">
              <span class="phase-num">Phase 01</span>
              <span class="phase-status" aria-label="foundation laid">✓</span>
            </div>
            <h3>Simulation</h3>
            <p>
              A virtual warehouse floor with arms, shuttles, and conveyors.
              Live state, a <strong>fail/recover lifecycle</strong>, and one
              <em>Docker container</em> per actor - one isolated service
              each. The base is solid; a Node-RED style builder is what's
              next.
            </p>
            <span class="phase-tag">Sprint 1-2 · iterating</span>
          </div>

          <div class="phase active">
            <div class="phase-head">
              <span class="phase-num">Phase 02</span>
              <span class="phase-status" aria-label="in progress">◐</span>
            </div>
            <h3>AI integration</h3>
            <p>
              Each actor gets its own <strong>small on-device brain</strong>
              running locally via Ollama. The brain interprets messages from
              the temporary backend and decides <em>when</em> and
              <em>which</em> script to run; the script handles <em>how</em>.
            </p>
            <span class="phase-tag">Sprint 3 · active</span>
          </div>

          <div class="phase pending">
            <div class="phase-head">
              <span class="phase-num">Phase 03</span>
              <span class="phase-status" aria-label="not started">○</span>
            </div>
            <h3>Actor coordination</h3>
            <p>
              The temporary backend goes away. Actors work out handovers
              between themselves on a <strong>shared message bus</strong>;
              the observer only steps in when peers get stuck.
            </p>
            <span class="phase-tag">Sprint 4+ · next up</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="phase-progress reveal">
          <span>start</span>
          <div class="track"><div class="marker"></div></div>
          <span>vision</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="slide-number">05<span class="of"> / 10</span></div>
    </section>

