              Every event streams to the browser over SocketIO. The sidebar
              shows what each actor is doing as it happens.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card cyan">
            <div class="icon">⚙</div>
            <h3>State machine defined</h3>
            <p>
              One contract covers every actor: idle, busy, draining, failed,
              recovering. All actors share the same machine.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="arch-callout reveal" style="margin-top: var(--element-gap)">
          <strong>Note: negative tests are still future work.</strong>
          What we have today covers the happy paths and the failure modes we
          already know about. The adversarial cases - weird timing, partial
          handovers, containers dying mid-cycle - are on the list, not done
          yet.
        </div>
